Description:
Image Description: The image shows a white wall with a significant area of peeling and cracked paint.

Repair needed: The damaged paint needs to be scraped off, the surface properly prepared, and repainted to prevent further deterioration and improve appearance.

Tradesman Required: A painter or a general handyman skilled in wall repairs and painting.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED.

Image Description: The image shows a deteriorated window sill with extensive wood rot. The wooden part is visibly damaged and crumbling, with exposed layers and fibers of wood.

Repair needed: The window sill needs to be completely replaced due to severe wood rot. This includes removing the damaged wood, treating the area to prevent further decay, and installing a new sill.

Tradesman Required: A carpenter or a window specialist is required to perform this repair.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED.

Image Description: The image shows the bottom corner of a wall near a window frame with visible signs of mold and deterioration. The paint on the wall is flaking and there are black mold spots along the wall and window frame.

Repair needed: Removal of mold, repair of the damaged wall surface, and repainting of the affected area.

Tradesman Required: A professional specializing in mold remediation and a painter to handle the wall repairs and repainting.

Mould Status: MOULD DETECTED.

Image Description: The image shows an interior room corner with significant mould growth on the walls. The mould appears to be extensive around the lower part of the wall near the floor and extends upwards. A radiator is present near the affected area, and there is a window above the radiator.

Repair Needed: The affected walls require mould remediation which includes cleaning the mould from the surfaces, treating the area to kill any remaining mould spores, and possibly repainting the area with mould-resistant paint. Additionally, it is important to identify and address any underlying issues such as leaks or condensation problems that may have contributed to the mould growth.

Tradesman Required: A professional mould remediation specialist or a qualified painter and decorator who is experienced in mould treatment is required to address this issue.

Mould Status: MOULD DETECTED.

Image Description: The image shows a close-up view of a broken window pane. The glass is shattered in several places with sharp, jagged edges visible. The window frame is made of dark-painted wood, and the sky reflecting on the unbroken part of the glass suggests the photo was taken during the day.

Repair needed: The broken window pane needs to be removed and replaced with a new piece of glass to ensure safety and restore the window's integrity.

Tradesman Required: A glazier is needed to handle the glass replacement professionally.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED

Image Description: The image shows the interior of a cabinet under a sink, displaying the plumbing setup. The cabinet's bottom surface has significant peeling and possible water damage, with patches of the underlying material exposed.

Repair needed: The cabinet floor needs resurfacing or replacement due to water damage and peeling of the finish.

Tradesman Required: A carpenter or a general handyman would be suitable for repairing the cabinet floor.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED

Image Description: The image shows a water leak in an indoor setting, likely in a room with large windows. Water has pooled on a dark wooden floor near the base of the windows, indicating a possible leak from the window or wall.

Repair needed: The source of the water leak needs to be identified and repaired to prevent further water damage. The wooden flooring may also require assessment for water damage restoration or replacement.

Tradesman Required: A plumber to investigate and repair the source of the leak, and possibly a carpenter or flooring specialist if the wooden floor has been significantly damaged.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED.

Image Description: The image displays the corner of a building where the roof meets the exterior wall. Visible is a damaged or improperly sealed joint where the roof overhang meets the vertical siding of the building. There appears to be some water damage or leakage evident from the discolored streaks along the siding and beneath the roof overhang.

Repair needed: The joint between the roof overhang and the siding needs to be inspected for structural integrity and water tightness. Repairs may include resealing the joint, replacing any damaged materials, and ensuring proper drainage at the junction to prevent future water ingress.

Tradesman Required: A roofing specialist or a general contractor with experience in roofing and exterior building repairs is required to address the issues.

Mould Status: MOULD NOT DETECTED

Image Description: The image shows a corner of a room with significant mold growth on the walls and damage to the floor. The walls are painted white, and the wooden floor appears to be parquet style. There is visible black and dark green mold growth concentrated mainly at the lower part of the walls, especially in the corner and spreading outward along the walls.

Repair needed: The affected walls need mold remediation and likely replacement of the damaged drywall sections. The floor also shows signs of water damage and may need repair or replacement in the affected area to prevent further damage and mold growth.

Tradesman Required: A mold remediation specialist is needed to address the mold issue and assess the extent of contamination. Following this, a general contractor or a carpenter might be required to repair or replace the damaged drywall and flooring.

Mould Status: MOULD DETECTED.

Image Description: The image shows a close-up view of a gutter on a building where debris, moss, and a small plant have accumulated. The gutter is attached to a roof with asphalt shingles, and it appears to be partially obstructed due to the buildup.

Repair needed: The gutter needs cleaning to remove the moss, plant, and other debris to ensure proper water flow and to prevent water damage or further accumulation. Additionally, inspect the gutter for any signs of damage or wear that might require repair or replacement.

Tradesman Required: A gutter cleaning service or a general handyman skilled in gutter maintenance is required for this job.

Mould Status: MOULD DETECTED.

Image Description:
The image shows a corner of a room where the wall meets the ceiling, displaying signs of water damage and peeling paint. The ceiling texture is rough, and there is visible discolouration and material breakdown. The floor is covered with a patterned vinyl flooring.

Repair needed:
The area requires treatment for water damage, including removal of the damaged paint, treatment of any affected underlying materials to prevent further deterioration, and repainting of the area. It is also necessary to investigate the source of moisture to prevent future damage.

Tradesman Required:
A general contractor or a specialist in water damage restoration should be consulted to assess and repair the damage.

Mould Status:
MOULD DETECTED. The discolouration and textural change in the materials suggest the presence of mould, which needs to be treated as part of the repair process.
